<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-713-469  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 713 469.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CAD-CAM International  Nov 1990 v9 n11 p15(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>In the know. (knowledge based engineering)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Clark, Charles.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Knowledge-based engineering (KBD) improves productivity, shortensthe design cycle by optimizing design and manufacturing processes,improves quality, reduces costs, and permits more designiterations.andP;  A KBE system has both the geometric and non-geometricinformation that defines the intent of the design.andP;  Two things mayhinder the growth of KBE: complex technology and confusion indefinition.andP;  The sales force must be educated to the benefits ofKBE.andP;  CAD, CAM, and computer-aided engineering software can workin conjunction with KBE.andP;  KBE will probably become a requiredfeature in any leading vendor's product portfolio.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Knowledge-Based SystemsEngineeringTrendsCAD/CAMComputer-Aided Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>